dsDescriptionValue.value:
"The CPI is a 480-item scale for assessing personality characteristics which have broad applicability to human behavior. It is intended for use with normal (vs pathological) subjects. The scales look at important aspects for social living and social interaction which can be grouped in the following categories: Measures of Poise, Ascendancy, Self Assurance and Interpersonal Adequacy; Measures of Socialization, Responsibility, Intrapersonal Values, and Character; Measures of Achievement Potenti al and Intellectual Efficiency; Measures of Intellect and Interest Modes; Factor Scales: Conventional Restraint, Assertive Self-Confidence Flexible Independence, Homely Virtue; Origence and Intellectence"

For each year, a merged file is called CPIM.

Scoring information is part of CAPS/88 source file.
